<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:40PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Lewis and
Clark and northwestern Jefferson Counties through 430 PM MDT...
At 339 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Basin, or 9 miles west of Boulder, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Boulder, Basin and Rimini.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
